wish weddings are known for their dancing.";i:11;s:168:"If theres one thing that most non-Jewish guests know about a Jewish wedding its that someone is going to be lifted on a chair and theres going to be some crazy dancing.";i:12;s:53:"Hora is a circular dance performed throughout Europe.";i:13;s:118:"All the participants stand in a circle holding each others hands and stepping right with the left foot and vice versa.";i:14;s:60:"The circle rotates from the right at the start of the music.";i:15;s:73:"The participants step to the side passing the left foot behind the right.";i:16;s:93:"Make sure you dance the hora before your chair lifters and the crowd gets too drunk or rowdy.";i:17;s:59:"We recommend dancing as soon as you can after the ceremony.";i:18;s:99:"A good time might be after cocktail hour or directly after the FatherDaughter and MotherSon dances.";i:19;s:74:"Pick your chair-lifters ahead of time and teach them how to lift properly.";i:20;s:71:"Hora medley jewish dance best version hava nagila by bobby morganstein.";i:21;s:86:"Well anyone and everyone who can and wants to be a part of the hora dance can join in.";i:22;s:59:"We recommend dancing as soon as you can after the ceremony.";i:23;s:95:"Guests hoist the bride and groom on chairs above the crowd to the traditional Hava Nagila song.";i:24;s:47:"Today dance also inspires spiritual expression.";i:25;s:28:"The Dance Steps of The Hora.";i:26;s:64:"So its no wonder that the hora is the norm-a at Jewish weddings.";i:27;s:45:"Its a time to celebrate and honor traditions.";i:28;s:91:"The hora also sometimes spelled horah is danced in 6 beats usually to the song Hava Nagila.";i:29;s:46:"Form a circle with your guests and hold hands.";i:30;s:30:"The Hora chair dance bailando.";i:31;s:24:"The Horah - Chair Dance.";i:32;s:81:"Hadassahs Wedding Hadassah and Irwin during the chair dance portion of the Horah.";i:33;s:220:"The Hora says Wikipedia is an Israeli circle dance typically danced to the music of Hava Nag